President Vladimir Putin of Russia signed the law establishing administrative liability for breaching the time and procedure for payment of goods (work, services) in procurement for public and municipal needs.
This law is designed to address the very acute problem of the failure of customers to comply with their obligations in public and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation in which entrepreneurs could not receive payment under existing public and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia instructed the Office of the Procurator-General of the Russian Federation to take the issue into special control.
Because businessmen themselves could not cope with unfair customers who entered into unfunded contracts, they tried to evade their obligations to pay and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in order to protect the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders from the Public Prosecutor ' s Office, 97,000 submissions have been made, 45,000 officials have been subject to disciplinary proceedings and 533 administrative cases have been brought before the investigating authorities for the conduct of procedural checks, of which 46 have been brought in criminal proceedings.
As a result, more than 66 billion roubles were owed to entrepreneurs.
These huge amounts have not been accumulated as a result of the non-payment of multi-million-dollar contracts.
Basque debt has resulted in numerous, systematic delays in the payment of services to entrepreneurs for a much more modest amount.
This is a typical case.
The manager of a small company won the social service competition for several million rubles.
The man invested all of his working capital, fully fulfilled his obligations, but did not receive the money in due course.
The result is a growing financial coma of salary, tax, credit that would result in bankruptcy if the entrepreneur had not sought assistance from the Public Prosecutor ' s Office.
The problem has now been maximized in a number of regions.
However, as at the first half of 2017, the total amount of public and municipal debt identified by the prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation was about 27.4 billion roubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the Public Prosecutor ' s Office operates under manual crisis management.
The Attorney-General personally holds visiting meetings with the local authorities, where all violations that have been discovered by prosecutors are thoroughly investigated and measures taken to address them without delay.
Such operational meetings have already taken place this year in Jaroslav and Ekaterinburg.
The implementation of Federal Act No. 189-FZ amending the Code of Administrative Offences of the Russian Federation with regard to the administrative liability of the employer ' s officials for breach of the time and procedure for the payment of goods (work, services) in procurement to ensure public and municipal needs, which was signed last week by the President of Russia, would greatly improve the payment discipline of public customers.
The draft law was drafted by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Attorney-General.
The new law will supplement the Code of Administrative Offences with an article that provides for a fine of between 30,000 and 50,000 roubles for breaching the employer ' s official ' s time and for payment of goods, works and services in public and municipal procurement.
If an official has already been administratively punished for a similar offence, he is awaiting disqualification for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure the application of these legislative innovations in practice.
