"If you're gonna ask for 4,000 sentences, you should be ready to hold 4,000 interviews," says Russell Rat, the president of the management consulting firm "Kotter International," who had to see companies making a mistake by relying too much on data collection.
"Because if you don't go to the end, the staff will wonder, "Did you really hear me?
